snippet.textDisplay:
Sørfugløyar means seabird-islands. Sør=sea, fugl=bird, øyar=islands. Pronounciation is a little hard to explain but I try. ø sounds like the german ö, it's a sound you dont really have in englich. it sounds somewhat like the "ir" ind "bird" or "sir", but still a little different. The G is silent, and "fugl" sounds almost just like "fool". So Sørfugløyar sounds kinda like Sir-fool-ir-yar"
Thatsthe best explanation I can give, I hope it was helpful
snippet.textOriginal:
